**b.** The standard deviation can be solved using this formula.

$$\begin{aligned}
\sqrt{\sigma^2}&=\dfrac{\sum(\text{x}-\text{mean})}{\text{n}-1}
\end{aligned}$$

To get the standard deviation for the inflation or the consumer price index, we will use the same concept.

$$\begin{aligned}
\sqrt{\sigma^2}&=\dfrac{(8.71-9.30)^2+(12.34-9.30)^2+(6.94-9.30)^2+(4.86-9.30)^2+(6.70-9.30)^2+(9.02-9.30)^2+(13.29-9.30)^2+(12.52-9.30)^2}{8-1}\\[15 pt]
&=\sqrt{9.71}
\end{aligned}$$
